SPECIAL INSTRUCTIONS FOR "XD" ROM ADAPTER
.br
.ps 10p
.vs 11p
.ce
Please read this page before installing your "XD" ROM.
.br


To help keep our product cost down, we now provide the "XD" ROM
with a special adapter socket.  This adapter allows us to use newer,
commonly-available EPROMs instead of the type originally used by your system.

When you reach the point in the instructions where it directs you to
install the
new "XD" ROM in the socket, simply plug the adapter (with the "XD" ROM already
attached) into the socket as the instructions indicate.

If you have a SmartWatch installed in the "D" ROM socket inside
your computer, read the following information:

The combination of the adapter, ROM and SmartWatch in the "D" ROM
sockets may be too tall to fit under the RF-shield in your machine.
If this is the case, we suggest you move the SmartWatch to the "A" 
ROM socket.  Most programs that read and set the SmartWatch work on
Model 4, 4D and 4P systems, so they should continue to work with the
SmartWatch located in the "A" ROM socket.

The following instructions detail how to use the SmartWatch with the adapter.
If you are not going to use the SmartWatch in the "D" ROM socket, ignore
these instructions.

.in .5i
.ti -.5i
1.	Remove the SmartWatch from your existing system and remove the old ROM.

.ti -.5i
2.	Remove and discard any jumper wires or adapter sockets that were used to
provide power to pin 28 of the SmartWatch.  These are no longer
necessary and could prevent proper operation.

.ti -.5i
3.	Carefully remove the new "XD" ROM from the adapter.  When handling
the adapter, take extra care to not bend the pins on the other
side of the adapter.  You might want to stick the pins into a piece of foam
while working with the adapter.

.ti -.5i
4.	Plug the SmartWatch into the adapter.  There is a "1" and "notch"
marking on the adapter to indicate proper insertion.  Note that the
zero-profile sockets on the adapter require that the pins be aligned
exactly.  If the SmartWatch is resisting being inserted, one or more pins are
not lining up.  When the pins are lined-up, the SmartWatch will plug in
easily.

.ti -.5i
5.	Plug the new "XD" ROM into the top of the SmartWatch.  Remember to
place pin 1 of the new "XD" ROM into pin 3 of the SmartWatch.  The old ROM was
plugged-into the same position.

.ti -.5i
6.	Now follow the original instructions and insert the adapter,
SmartWatch and new "XD" ROM as a single unit.

.in 0i
.br
If the use of the adapter is unacceptable to you, return it, along with
all documentation, diskettes, packaging and the new
ROM.  We will exchange it for an old-style ROM, or, if they are not
available, we will refund the purchase price.


